  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to compare telemedical antihypertensive treatment based on home blood
      pressure monitoring and conventional antihypertensive treatment based on monitoring of blood
      pressure in the doctor's office.

      We want to test the hypotheses that telemedical treatment is more effective in lowering blood
      pressure, provide better quality of life and is more cost-effective.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
